Description: A tint is a single process color applied to the roots and hair shaft. It is used for root touch up, grey coverage, and enhancing color throughout.

Service: Bright – Lactic Peel 20% with Kojic and Arbutin
Description: Lactic acid is a gentle, hydrating, alpha hydroxy acid. The solution resurfaces, firms, and evens out skin tone. Arbutin and Kojic acid fade hyperpigmentation. Ideal for peel first-timers. Recovery is minimal to none.

Glycolic acid, an alpha hydroxy acid, exfoliates dull surface skin cells, reduces the appearance of sun damage, smoothes fine lines, promotes collagen growth and attracts moisture to the skin. Slightly deeper than the lactic peel, glycolic is adjustable and versatile to all skin types. Recovery is minimal to none.

Service: Clear – Cranberry Peel 20% Salicylic Acid + Extended Extractions
Description: Salicylic acid is an oil-dissolving beta hydroxy acid. The solution resurfaces and refines skin and pores and banishes bacteria. Extended extractions are included with this treatment. Ideal for very oily and/or acneic skin. Recovery may include flaking and peeling 3-4 days post treatment.
Noticeably firms facial contours and smoothes skin texture, resulting in a more radiant, youthful appearance.
